The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Loose Change
                                                                                                                 LOOSE CHANGE
                              
	 Mirae Asset Global Investment Management (India) Pvt Ltd, the latest entrant in the mutual fund industry, has launched its first scheme, India Opportunities Fund. It is an open-ended equity- oriented scheme that is open till March 10. The fund will invest a minimum of 65 per cent of its corpus in domestic equities and equity- related securities. The scheme will also invest up to 25 per cent in securitised debt.                             
	 Star Health amp; Allied Insurance has introduced Star Super Surplus Insurance Policy. This policy is primarily for persons between the age group of 5 months and 65 years and comes with a fixed premium irrespective of the age of the person. There are two options under this policy. The sum insured under the first option would be Rs 7 lakh at an annual premium of Rs 3,000. The second option has a higher insured sum of Rs 10 lakh at an annual premium of Rs 4,000.                             
	 UTI-SPrEAD Fund has declared a tax-free dividend of 8 per cent, or 80 paise per unit, on a face value of Rs 10. Pursuant to the payment of dividend, the NAV of the dividend option of the scheme will fall to the extent of payout and statutory levy. The record date for the dividend is February 19.                                                                                                                                
